# Per-run artifacts written by benchmark runs into fixture HOMEs.
# Each fixture is a fake $HOME — qwen-code writes profile reports, debug logs,
# chat history, OAuth state, settings backups, etc. into it. None of that
# should be committed.
#
# Allow only the canonical files we author by hand (settings.json + the MCP
# server fixtures) and ignore everything else.

# Anywhere under .qwen/
*/.qwen/startup-perf/
*/.qwen/debug/
*/.qwen/oauth/
*/.qwen/chats/
*/.qwen/sessions/
*/.qwen/output-language.md
*/.qwen/installation_id
*/.qwen/settings.json.orig
*/.qwen/skills/
*/.qwen/tmp/

# Fixture roots (HOME-level artifacts qwen-code writes outside .qwen/)
*/debug/
*/installation_id
*/output-language.md
*/.bash_history
*/.npm/
*/.cache/

# Migration-flag files
*/.qwen/migration-version
